As our implementation is very much in a work-in-progress phase and
currently focuses on the feasibility of compiling programs with holes, we
do not yet have benchmarks for incomplete programs. A comparison with
the evaluator on fully complete programs identifies that Grain's runtime is
quite slow, making the compiler hardly comparable with the evaluator,
but draws no conclusions about our design; we may want to replace our
backend with something faster in future work.
